COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. WOODMERE CEMETERY ASSOCIATION. No. 7546. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 8, 1938. Robert H. Jackson, Sewall Key, Herman Oliphant, James W. Morris, Morrison Shafroth, and Frank M. Thompson, all of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. James K. Watkins, of Detroit, Mich., for respondent.

Before HICKS,’ SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.,

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed, pursitant to stipulation of counsel.
